## Public Member Attributes

### ExposesExternalVFSPath {#a6cac50145861d6d1596b5825ce0142ea}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="bool llvm::vfs::Status::ExposesExternalVFSPath = false">
Whether this entity has an external path different from the virtual path, and the external path is exposed by leaking it through the abstraction.

For example, a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vfs/redirectingfilesystem">RedirectingFileSystem</a> will set this for paths where UseExternalName is true.

FIXME: Currently the external path is exposed by replacing the virtual path in this <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vfs/status">Status</a> object. Instead, we should leave the path in the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vfs/status">Status</a> intact (matching the requested virtual path) - see FileManager::getFileRef for how we plan to fix this.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/virtualfilesystem-h/#l00068">68</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/virtualfilesystem-h">VirtualFileSystem.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

</SectionDefinition>
